From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: conda-forge <conda-forge@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 16 Dec 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix jbig2dec callback signature compatibility

The jbig2dec library changed the Jbig2ErrorCallback signature to use
'int' instead of 'uint32_t' for the segment index parameter.

---
 source/fitz/filter-jbig2.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/source/fitz/filter-jbig2.c b/source/fitz/filter-jbig2.c
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/source/fitz/filter-jbig2.c
+++ b/source/fitz/filter-jbig2.c
@@ -163,7 +163,7 @@ struct fz_jbig2d_s
 };

 static void
-error_callback(void *data, const char *msg, Jbig2Severity severity, uint32_t seg_idx)
+error_callback(void *data, const char *msg, Jbig2Severity severity, int seg_idx)
 {
 	fz_context *ctx = data;
 	char idxbuf[50] = "";
